abstract: The West Virginia Democrat, who dashed President Trump’s hopes for a bipartisan acquittal, said his vote to convict was not about politics.
snippet: The West Virginia Democrat, who dashed President Trump’s hopes for a bipartisan acquittal, said his vote to convict was not about politics.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Joe Manchin III votes with President Trump more than any other Democrat in the Senate. But his vote last week to convict Mr. Trump of impeachable offenses has eclipsed all of that, earning him the rage of a president who coveted a bipartisan acquittal.

abstract: With the possibility of five leading candidates surviving beyond New Hampshire, the prospect of a long contest looms large.
snippet: With the possibility of five leading candidates surviving beyond New Hampshire, the prospect of a long contest looms large.
lead_paragraph: EXETER, N.H. — The Democratic presidential candidates amplified their attacks on one another on Monday in the final hours before polls open in New Hampshire, highlighting the deep divisions between the party’s left and center even as their campaigns prepared for a set of even more pivotal contests in the weeks ahead.

abstract: After Joe Biden’s fourth-place finish in Iowa, some supporters fear that a damaging result in Tuesday’s primary could hurt his financial resources to compete in later contests.
snippet: After Joe Biden’s fourth-place finish in Iowa, some supporters fear that a damaging result in Tuesday’s primary could hurt his financial resources to compete in later contests.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — His donors and supporters around the country are uneasy. His poll numbers in New Hampshire and nationally look increasingly shaky. He faces intense competition for moderate Democratic support and uncertainty about his viability in future contests.

abstract: Noting that investigators must consider any information potentially relevant to their work, the attorney general said that evidence from Ukraine could not be taken “at face value.”
snippet: Noting that investigators must consider any information potentially relevant to their work, the attorney general said that evidence from Ukraine could not be taken “at face value.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Attorney General William P. Barr said on Monday that the Justice Department would consider information from Rudolph W. Giuliani, President Trump’s personal lawyer, about Ukraine. That could include assertions about former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and his son Hunter.

abstract: A projected 32 million Latinos will be able to head to the polls in November. The Democratic presidential campaigns are hoping to engage them.
snippet: A projected 32 million Latinos will be able to head to the polls in November. The Democratic presidential campaigns are hoping to engage them.
lead_paragraph: ﻿﻿A record 32 million Latinos are projected to be eligible to vote this November, putting them on track to become the largest minority voting bloc. They are far from single-issue voters, with education, health care, jobs, the economy and immigration all ranking as top concerns.

headline_main: Cruise Ship, Oscars, North Korea: Your Tuesday Briefing

abstract: For Jeff Sessions, Roy Moore and other Republicans vying for a chance to take back Doug Jones’s seat, winning over voters may mean winning over the president first.
snippet: For Jeff Sessions, Roy Moore and other Republicans vying for a chance to take back Doug Jones’s seat, winning over voters may mean winning over the president first.
lead_paragraph: In early November, President Trump announced he would be traveling to Tuscaloosa, Ala., to attend the University of Alabama-Louisiana State University football game. When Representative Bradley Byrne, a three-term congressman and United States Senate candidate from Mobile, learned of this plan, he immediately called an Alabama booster named Jim Wilson, who would be hosting Trump in his luxury box near midfield at Bryant-Denny Stadium. Wilson, as fortune would have it, is a distant relative, friend and financial supporter of Byrne’s, and Byrne thought perhaps he could get him into the box.
